JOS – A Plateau State former deputy governor, Ignatious Longjan, the current senator representing Plateau South Senatorial District in the National Assembly, has called for federal presence in his district. Senator Longjan made this demand in Jos while speaking with newsmen in Jos shortly after he case at the National/ state Houses of Assemblies electoral tribunal. According to him, lobbying for federal presence at Plateau South Senatorial district calls for close collaboration with other lawmakers from his zone and Political appointees in consultation with Governor Simon Lalong who is also from the zone in the state. Longjan assured his constituents that since his Senatorial district is backward in so many things, he was going to work round the clock to provide dividends of democracy to the people to justify the confidence they repose in him as their elected senator representing them at the Senate.